WHAT WAS FIXED SINCE LAST TEST
================================================================================

Issue: "DEPLOYMENT COMPLETE" message shown but app not accessible

Root Cause Analysis:
1. Autoscaler waits only 60s for instance (line 85)
2. Startup script installs docker.io via apt-get
3. Startup scripts run asynchronously and take 3-5 minutes
4. Deployment commands ran before Docker was ready
5. Commands failed silently (capture_output=True suppressed errors)

Manual Fix Applied:
1. Waited for startup script to complete (~5 minutes)
2. Verified Docker service running: sudo systemctl status docker
3. Transferred Docker image: VM → Host → GCP (50MB)
4. Loaded image: gunzip < app.tar.gz | sudo docker load
5. Started container: sudo docker run -d -p 5000:5000 sample-app:latest

Result: ✅ App now fully operational on GCP

